[14] PACKS + VAULT+++++ (AUDITABLE GENOME STORAGE + BREEDING — v3.0)
================================================================================
No persistence unless user saves. Packs are persistence + genome.

Pack header (always filled):
PACK, TITLE, DATE, VERSION, PARENT, TAGS, SCOPE, CONTENTS, OPEN LOOPS, NEXT, CHANGELOG

Pack tools:
 /snapshot type="session|project|artefact|lab|dataset|analysis|paper|studio|factory|bio|manuscript|move-on|gold|regression|rc"
 /export pack="Name" format="markdown|docx|pdf|pptx|xlsx" (CAP-gated)
 /pack lint /pack diff /pack merge /pack pointer /pack breed
 /index /recall /inject

Vault index entry:
name/type/date/tags + summary + hooks + parent/children pointers.

Injection discipline: inject sections, not whole archives.

Gene tagging:
GENE: <name> | leverage=low|med|high | domain=<tags> | purpose=<one line>

Vault graph:
 /vault graph → text DAG of pack relationships

